From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hermes Agent <hermes@nousresearch.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: ARM: dts: sun8i-h3: Replace NanoPi H3 common dtsi with FriendlyElec
 version

Adapt FriendlyElec's comprehensive sun8i-h3-nanopi.dtsi (kernel 4.14.111)
for mainline kernel 6.x compatibility. This adds full board support:
  - HDMI connector with audio (sound_hdmi)
  - GPIO LEDs with custom labels (status_led, LED2)
  - GPIO power button (K1)
  - vdd_cpux gpio-regulator with CPU OPPs
  - I2S audio with PCM5102A DAC
  - Regulators for vcc1v2, vcc-dram, vdd-cpux-en
  - Thermal cooling maps
  - All EHCI/OHCI USB ports (0-3)
  - MMC0 (SD) and MMC2 (eMMC) support
  - Full pinctrl for LEDs, SPI CS
  - UART0-3, I2C0-2, SPI0/SPI1
  - SPI0 with spidev, spiflash (MX25L12805D), PiTFT (ST7789V) and touch
  - HDMI/TCON/mixer/DE display pipeline
  - I2S0/I2S2 audio
  - EMAC local-mac-address placeholder
  - Codec audio routing
  - PWM (disabled by default)
  - USB OTG with regulator
  - IR receiver (disabled by default)

Adapted pinctrl references for kernel 6.18:
  - mmc0_pins_a -> mmc0_pins
  - uart0_pins_a -> uart0_pa_pins
  - pwm0_pins -> removed (no separate PWM pinctrl in 6.18)
  - ir_pins_a -> r_ir_rx_pin

